Text: this happened about 8 months ago, at the time i was working in a small brewery. i had just finished cooking a 400 litter batch of beer and transferred it into a fermentation tank through a pipe that goes to a valve at the bottom of the tank, at this point i was done with the part in which i had to be concentrated, so i turned on some music and was getting ready for last 30 minutes of cleanups before i close up.

&nbsp;

i had to disconnect the pipe that is connected to the fermentation tank in order to wash it, now here is the fuck up, in a lack of concentration i reached my hand under the tank and disconnected it without looking, thing is, instead of disconnecting the pipe from the valve i disconnected the valve from tank, immediately the valve flew off and beer started gushing out soaking me wet, it took me a few seconds to realize what just happened in which point i started trying to stop the flow of beer with my hand. now that is no easy task, i had to push my legs against a wall and use the force of my whole body to push my hand onto the hole while turning my head to the side because the beer was spraying everywhere, ones the flow stopped it was easy to hold it closed, but now i needed the valve which is not within the reach of my hand, i had to lay down with my whole body on the beer soaked floor and drag it towards me with my legs, ones i got it i was able to reconnect it and shout the tank.

&nbsp;

i had to take the bus home still all soaked in beer .

&nbsp;

i later found out that about 150 litters of beer was spilled and the rest was contaminated and could not be sold, luckily for me my boss is a great guy and he wasn't even that angry.

&nbsp;
&nbsp;
